A CLASSY FASHION UPGRADE WITH BLAZERS FOR MEN

With its origins as jackets for boating and maritime activities, blazers for men have come a long way. The word 'blazer' is derived from the name of a boat - its crew wore blue and white striped jackets. At Myntra we are host to some of the best blazers for men.

Our blazer brands feature a variety of fabrics, styling, patterns and shades. Choose your favourites and upgrade your formal wear ensemble in an instant. We bring you the best price blazers for men in town. You can buy as many affordable varieties as you like for each occasion.

BLAZERS FOR MEN - EXPLORING STYLES

Gents blazers can be used to style up any outfit - be it shirt and trousers, or T-shirt and jeans combinations. They are also functional as they keep you warm in the winters.

Here is a look at how to choose from among different types of men’s blazer styles available at our online store:

  1. You can start with notched lapel men’s blazers online, which are versatile and suitable for most body types. Choose a single-breasted black blazer for everyday business suits. Or get a slim-fit grey blazer for a winning look at a job interview. Opt for a smart-casual blazer in navy blue checks, teamed up with a bright V-neck T-shirt, chinos and derbies - impress all the ladies at a posh pub.
  2. Peaked lapel blazers for men offer a bolder look. You can wear it for a big formal occasion or a special event such as a Christmas party or even weddings.
  3. Choose a brown double-breasted blazer with peaked lapels. Wear it with a white shirt, grey trousers and brown brogues for a big business presentation. You could also opt for a blue blazer with self-design patterns. Wear it with blue trousers and a lightly patterned tie for a wedding event.
  4. Shawl-collar blazers are more formal and flashy. They are used exclusively for black-tie events and red-carpet occasions. Choose a navy striped tuxedo blazer which comes with a pocket square. Wear it with a white shirt with polka dots, a blue bow tie and oxfords.
  5. You can create a strikingly smart ethnic or semi-formal outfit with the help of waistcoats. Attend a Sangeet function dressed in a kurta-pyjama combination worn with mojari shoes. Layer it up with a smart jacquard woven-design sleeveless waistcoat, with a mandarin collar. Or go for a fusion look with a short kurta-trousers combination matched with a Nehru jacket and derby shoes.

Try blended woollen coat for winters, and funnel coats with T-shirt and jeans for a style makeover.
